So, we are going in after him that afternoon. In the meantime, team member Davey Stuckey is after a double drop tine buck at his place in Ohio on opening day as well. We will finish up with my son Briar as we try to get him his first deer ever with a compound. It is an exciting group of hunts to start off season 5 so let's get right to it!

programme.title: King 8
programme.desc: t's time to get down to business. Late October is here and I am making my annual run through the midwest. The first stop is Illinois. Although the past few years have been tough in Illinois, I have high hopes to come within bow range of 2 different bucks I have been following on my Spartan Cameras. We timed this trip up strategically with the Red Moon because I know that gets the deer on their feet and especially the big mature bucks. Our first afternoon sit, we are in the game right off the bat and I am confident that with a little adjustment to our set up we will be right in the game. On day number 2 we pulled a hang and hunt and you just have to watch and see what happened. Let's just say he could not handle the grunt call from Illusion Systems and he wasn't the only one. Just watch and see this epic hunt from Illinois in late October.

programme.title: DKM
programme.desc: Join us this week as team member Kyle Kinsey goes after a dream buck. We have all dreamed of seeing a monster buck with a drop tine let alone killing one. Kyle was monitoring this deer all summer long on his Spartan Cameras and was all in on this buck he nicknamed DKM. As patternable as he was during the early season, he gave Kyle the slip and went nocturnal. It wasn't until early November during the Red Moon on a perfect afternoon during the rut where Kyle was able to lay eyes on DKM for the first time. After seeing 14 bucks running wild, DKM finally showed himself and the rest is history. Here is the story of the infamous DKM.

programme.title: Shed
